<inglise> Council Regulation (EC) No 657/2000 of 27 March 2000 on closer dialogue with the fishing sector and groups affected by the common fisheries policy </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 657/2000 kalandussektori ja &uuml;hise kalanduspoliitika m&otilde;jualasse kuuluvate r&uuml;hmade vahelise dialoogi t&otilde;hustamise kohta 27. m&auml;rts 2000 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 37 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 37, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament, Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) In order to give the representatives of the fishery products and aquaculture industry together with the other groups concerned a greater role in the design, drafting and implementation of the common fisheries policy (CFP), it is necessary to establish closer dialogue with these groups and to make the entire decision-making process more transparent, especially in the preparatory stages. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) selleks et anda kalandus- ja akvakultuuritoodete t&ouml;&ouml;stuse esindajatele ning asjaomastele r&uuml;hmadele rohkem v&otilde;imalusi &uuml;hise kalanduspoliitika kujundamisel, v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamisel ja rakendamisel, on vaja t&otilde;hustada nimetatud r&uuml;hmade vahelist dialoogi ja muuta kogu otsuste tegemise protsess l&auml;bipaistvamaks eelk&otilde;ige algetappidel; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) In view of the tasks of the Advisory Committee on Fisheries and Aquaculture (ACFA) renewed under Commission Decision 1999/478/EC(1), these objectives of closer dialogue and transparency could be made easier by the introduction of new measures to improve the organisation of meetings of the ACFA, on the one hand, and the communication to the groups concerned of information concerning the issues at stake and the results achieved, on the other. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) silmas pidades komisjoni otsusega 1999/478/E&Uuml; (1) uuendatud kalanduse ja akvakultuuri n&otilde;uandekomitee &uuml;lesandeid, on v&otilde;imalik tihedama dialoogi ja l&auml;bipaistvusega seotud eesm&auml;rke lihtsamini saavutada, kehtestades &uuml;helt poolt uued kalanduse ja akvakultuuri n&otilde;uandekomitee istungite korraldamise t&otilde;hustamise meetmed ning edastades teiselt poolt asjaomastele r&uuml;hmadele teavet arutuse all olevate k&uuml;simuste ja saavutatud tulemuste kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) To that end, the European trade organisations should be given help in preparing meetings of the ACFA with a view to stimulating comprehensive study of the issues involved in the CFP and the impact of its measures, fostering initiatives from the industry and seeking, if possible, common positions on Commission draft proposals. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) seet&otilde;ttu tuleks Euroopa kutseorganisatsioonidel aidata ette valmistada kalanduse ja akvakultuuri n&otilde;uandekomitee istungeid, et soodustada &uuml;hise kalanduspoliitika reguleerimisalasse kuuluvate k&uuml;simuste ja k&otilde;nealuse poliitika meetmete rakendamise tulemuste igak&uuml;lgset uurimist, edendada t&ouml;&ouml;stusharu algatusi ja saavutada v&otilde;imaluse korral &uuml;hisseisukoht komisjoni ettepanekute eeln&otilde;ude suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) In order to improve the circumstances in which decisions are taken the industry should be informed at a very early stage of the initiatives planned and the aims and details of the different CFP measures should be explained to all the groups concerned, </inglise>
<eesti> 4) t&auml;iendamaks otsuste tegemisega seotud asjaolusid, tuleks teavitada t&ouml;&ouml;stust kavandatavatest algatustest nende algetapil ja k&otilde;ikidele asjaomastele r&uuml;hmadele tuleks &uuml;ksikasjalikult selgitada &uuml;hise kalanduspoliitika erinevaid meetmeid, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Within the conditions laid down in the Annex, the Commission shall bear the cost of: </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon kannab lisas s&auml;testatud tingimustel kulud, mis on seotud: </eesti>
<inglise> - meetings arranged by the European trade organisations which are aimed at preparing meetings of the Advisory Committee on Fisheries and Aquaculture, </inglise>
<eesti> - Euroopa kutseorganisatsioonide korraldatud istungitega, mille &uuml;lesanne on valmistada ette kalanduse ja akvakultuuri n&otilde;uandekomitee istungeid, </eesti>
<inglise> - explaining the objectives of, and measures relating to, the common fisheries policy, and in particular Commission proposals, and of disseminating relevant information in this field to the fishing industry and the groups concerned, maintaining regular contact with the organisations and groups concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> - &uuml;hise kalanduspoliitika eesm&auml;rkide ja sellega seotud meetmete, eelk&otilde;ige komisjoni ettepanekute selgitamisega ning k&otilde;nealust valdkonda k&auml;sitleva asjakohase teabe edastamisega kalat&ouml;&ouml;stusele ja selle asjaomastele r&uuml;hmadele, s&auml;ilitades korrap&auml;rased sidemed asjaomaste organisatsioonide ja r&uuml;hmadega. </eesti>
<inglise> Funding may be provided also for meetings of experts arranged by the Commission to support the activities referred to in the second indent of the first subparagraph. </inglise>
<eesti> Rahastada v&otilde;ib ka ekspertide kohtumisi, mille komisjon on korraldanud, et toetada esimese l&otilde;igu teises taandes osutatud tegevust. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The Commission may carry out all the verifications it considers necessary to ensure compliance with the conditions and performance of the tasks assigned by this Regulation to the European trade organisations, which shall assist the representatives appointed for this purpose by the Commission. </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjon v&otilde;ib teha mis tahes vajaliku kontrolli, et tagada tingimuste ja &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmist, mis k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega on pandud neile Euroopa kutseorganisatsioonidele, kes abistavad selleks komisjoni poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud esindajaid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following that of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 27 March 2000. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 27. m&auml;rts 2000 </eesti>
